The City of Joburg says it wants to write off about R11.7 billion, as part of its debt rehabilitation programme. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Some relief for Joburg residents struggling to keep their accounts paid and up to date. Many of whom have been financially impacted by COVID-19. The City of Joburg says it wants to write off about R11.7 billion, as part of its debt rehabilitation programme. READ: Billing crisis: Joburg resident sitting with hefty R100,000 electricity bill Residents in arrears and who meet the criteria can apply to have their debts written off. eNCA's Khayelihle Khumalo shares more details in the video above.